🔹 Git & GitHub – 10 Q&A

Q1. What is the difference between git pull and git fetch?
ans= git fetch downloads new changes but does not merge them.
 git pull = git fetch + git merge (brings changes into local branch).

Q2. How do you resolve a merge conflict in Git?
 Run git status → open conflicting files → manually fix conflict markers → git add <file> → git commit.

Q3. Difference between git rebase and git merge?
👉 merge: keeps history, adds a merge commit.
👉 rebase: rewrites history, cleaner linear flow.

Q4. How do you revert a commit already pushed to GitHub?
👉 Use git revert <commit-id> → creates a new commit that undoes changes.

Q5. Explain Git branching strategies.
👉 GitFlow: master, develop, feature, release, hotfix.
👉 Trunk-based: small, frequent merges into main.

Q6. How do you squash commits?
👉 git rebase -i HEAD~n → mark commits as squash.

Q7. Difference between bare repo and working repo?
👉 Bare repo: no working directory (used in servers).
👉 Working repo: has .git + code.

Q8. Your branch is behind origin/main, what do you do?
👉 git pull --rebase origin main to update branch with latest code.

Q9. What is GitHub Actions?
👉 A CI/CD tool inside GitHub → automates build, test, deploy workflows using YAML files.

Q10. How do you protect the main branch?
👉 Enable branch protection rules: require PR reviews, block direct pushes, enforce status checks.

🔹 Jenkins – 10 Q&A

Q1. Explain Jenkins architecture.
👉 Jenkins Master (control, scheduling) + Agents (execute builds).

Q2. Declarative vs Scripted pipeline?
👉 Declarative: simple, structured (pipeline {} syntax).
👉 Scripted: flexible, Groovy-based scripting.

Q3. Trigger Jenkins job on Git push?
👉 Configure webhook in GitHub → Jenkins Git plugin → Poll SCM or webhook trigger.

Q4. Difference between freestyle and pipeline jobs?
👉 Freestyle: GUI-based, limited flexibility.
👉 Pipeline: code-as-pipeline (Jenkinsfile), reusable & version-controlled.

Q5. How to secure Jenkins?
👉 Use RBAC, LDAP/AD, mask secrets, HTTPS, restrict anonymous access.

Q6. Handle credentials securely?
👉 Jenkins Credentials plugin → store secrets → use withCredentials block.

Q7. Integrate Jenkins with Docker/Kubernetes?
👉 Run builds in Docker agents.
👉 Use Kubernetes plugin to spin up ephemeral agents.

Q8. Approval stages in pipeline?
👉 input step → manual approval before continuing.

Q9. Jenkins shared libraries?
👉 Centralized reusable Groovy scripts across pipelines.

Q10. Scale Jenkins?
👉 Use multiple agents, Kubernetes dynamic agents, split jobs into different controllers.

🔹 Kubernetes – 10 Q&A

Q1. Deployment vs ReplicaSet vs StatefulSet vs DaemonSet?
👉 Deployment → stateless apps.
👉 ReplicaSet → manages replicas.
👉 StatefulSet → stateful apps (databases).
👉 DaemonSet → runs pod on every node.

Q2. Role of etcd?
👉 Distributed key-value store → holds entire cluster state. or it is a database for our application.

Q3. Service types?
👉 ClusterIP (internal), NodePort (external via node) 30000 - 32767, LoadBalancer (cloud LB), Ingress (HTTP routing).

Q4. Rolling updates & rollbacks?
👉 kubectl rollout status deployment → update.
👉 kubectl rollout undo deployment → rollback.

Q5. ConfigMap vs Secret?
👉 ConfigMap: non-sensitive configs.
👉 Secret: sensitive (base64 encoded).
Echo password | base64 --encoded

Q6. Pod in CrashLoopBackOff?
👉 Check logs (kubectl logs), describe pod (kubectl get describe), check env vars, probes, resource limits.

Q7. HPA vs VPA?
👉 HPA: scales pods horizontally (replicas) or increse number of pods.
👉 VPA: adjusts CPU/memory requests.

Q8. Secure cluster?
👉 RBAC, TLS, secrets, network policies, namespaces.

Q9. kube-proxy vs kubelet?
👉 kube-proxy: networking, service routing.
👉 kubelet: manages pods on node.

Q10. Monitoring cluster?
👉 Prometheus + Grafana, CloudWatch, ELK.

🔹 Docker – 10 Q&A

Q1. Docker image vs container?
👉 Image: blueprint.
👉 Container: running instance.

Q2. Dockerfile best practices?
👉 Use small base image, .dockerignore, multi-stage builds, pin versions.

Q3. Reduce image size?
👉 Alpine base, clean cache, multi-stage builds.

Q4. Multi-stage builds?
👉 Build app in one stage, copy only needed artifacts into final stage.

Q5. COPY vs ADD? 
👉 COPY → simple file copy.
👉 ADD → supports remote URLs & tar extraction.

Q6. Handle container logs?
👉 docker logs <id>, log drivers (json, fluentd, ELK).

Q7. Docker Compose vs Swarm?
👉 Compose: multi-container setup on single host.
👉 Swarm: clustering, orchestration or multi-container runs on multiple hosts.

Q8. Connect multiple containers?
👉 Use Docker networks (docker network create).

Q9. Scan images?
👉 Use Trivy, Clair, Anchore.

Q10. ENTRYPOINT vs CMD?
👉 ENTRYPOINT → fixed main command.
👉 CMD → default arguments.


🔹 Terraform – 10 Q&A

Q1. What is Terraform state file? Why remote backend?
👉 State tracks infra resources. Remote backend (S3 + DynamoDB lock) ensures collaboration, consistency, and no conflicts.

Q2. Difference between terraform plan and terraform apply?
👉 plan shows changes (dry run), apply executes and provisions resources.

Q3. State locking?
👉 DynamoDB table locks state → prevents multiple apply at same time.

Q4. Terraform modules?
👉 Reusable code blocks (network, EC2, VPC). Helps DRY & consistency.

Q5. Manage multiple environments?
👉 Workspaces (terraform workspace new dev), or directory structure (dev/test/prod).

Q6. Handle secrets in Terraform?
👉 Use SSM Parameter Store, Secrets Manager, Vault → never hardcode.

Q7. Terraform vs CloudFormation?
👉 Terraform: multi-cloud, HCL language.
👉 CloudFormation: AWS-only, JSON/YAML.

Q8. Upgrade provider versions?
👉 Update required_providers block → run terraform init -upgrade.

Q9. terraform import?
👉 Brings existing AWS resources under Terraform management.

Q10. Troubleshoot terraform apply fail?
👉 Check plan output, logs, provider config, permissions (IAM).

Ansible – 10 Q&A

Q1. Ad-hoc vs Playbook?
👉 Ad-hoc: one-time tasks (ansible all -m ping).
👉 Playbook: YAML-defined automation, reusable.

Q2. Inventory file role?
👉 Defines managed hosts (static or dynamic). Example: /etc/ansible/hosts.

Q3. Handle secrets?
👉 Ansible Vault → encrypt passwords/keys (ansible-vault encrypt).

Q4. What are roles?
👉 Pre-structured format with tasks, handlers, vars, templates, defaults, files.

Q5. Push vs Pull mode?
👉 Push = default (Ansible pushes tasks).
👉 Pull = nodes pull config via cron.

Q6. Test playbooks?
👉 Use ansible-playbook --check --diff, Molecule testing.

Q7. Difference between when and register?
👉 when: conditional execution.
👉 register: store command output for later use.

Q8. Ansible for AWS provisioning?
👉 Use AWS modules (ec2, s3, rds) with IAM credentials.

Q9. Reuse variables across playbooks?
👉 group_vars/, host_vars/, vars_files:.

Q10. Idempotency?
👉 Running playbook multiple times won’t change system if already in desired state.

🔹 Linux – 10 Q&A

Q1. Find CPU & memory usage?
👉 top, htop, free -m, vmstat.

Q2. Hard link vs Soft link?
👉 Hard link → same inode, works if original deleted.
👉 Soft link → shortcut (symbolic), breaks if original deleted.

Q3. chmod 755 meaning?
👉 Owner: read/write/execute.
👉 Group & others: read/execute only.

Q4. Check process on a port?
👉 netstat -tulnp | grep <port> 

Q5. Difference grep vs egrep vs fgrep?
👉 grep = basic regex, egrep = extended regex, fgrep = fixed string.

Q6. Monitor logs real-time?
👉 tail -f /var/log/syslog or journalctl -f.

Q7. cron vs systemd timers?
👉 Cron: traditional scheduler.
👉 systemd timers: modern, more reliable, logs integrated.

Q8. Find top 10 largest files?
👉 du -ah /path | sort -rh | head -n 10.

Q9. kill -9 vs kill -15?
👉 -15 (SIGTERM) → graceful shutdown.
👉 -9 (SIGKILL) → force kill.

Q10. Troubleshoot disk full?
👉 df -h, du -sh *, clean logs/tmp files, rotate logs.

🔹 Tomcat – 10 Q&A

Q1. What is Apache Tomcat?
👉 Open-source Java servlet container (runs JSP/Servlets). Not a full JEE app server.

Q2. Deploy WAR file?
👉 Place .war in webapps/ → auto-deployed.

Q3. Important config files?
👉 server.xml, web.xml, context.xml, tomcat-users.xml.

Q4. Difference between server.xml and web.xml?
👉 server.xml: server-level configs (ports, connectors).
👉 web.xml: app-level configs (servlets, filters).

Q5. Change Tomcat port?
👉 Edit <Connector port="8080"> in server.xml.

Q6. Enable HTTPS/SSL?
👉 Generate keystore → update server.xml with SSL connector.

Q7. Tomcat logs location?
👉 logs/ directory → catalina.out, localhost.log, manager.log.

Q8. Performance tuning?
👉 Tune JVM heap, thread pool (server.xml), enable GZIP compression.

Q9. Load balancing Tomcat?
👉 Use Apache HTTPD/NGINX with mod_jk/mod_proxy → forward to Tomcat cluster.

Q10. Troubleshoot app not starting?
👉 Check catalina.out, verify WAR deployment, JVM memory, conflicts in server.xml.
